🌍 What happens in other languages?

Languages that behave similarly

They map physical → emotional weight the same way, so it still works:
	•	Spanish language: pesado (heavy) can also imply burden
	•	French language: lourd (heavy) can mean oppressive/serious
	•	German language: schwer = heavy and difficult/serious

👉 In these, your line mostly survives intact

⸻

Languages that split the concepts more

Some languages separate physical weight from emotional weight more clearly.

Example tendencies (simplified):
	•	One word for mass
	•	Another for importance / seriousness

In those cases:
	•	Your exact phrasing loses its punch
	•	You’d have to rebuild the metaphor

